                  <a href="index.html?p=28" title="Permalink to: Use Comments to Organize Your CSS Design">
                    Use Comments to Organize Your CSS Design                  </a>
                </p>
              
              
              
                              <p class="post-excerpt">It’s inevitable: the longer you work with CSS, the longer your CSS files will grow. And the longer your files get, the tougher it will be to find what you’re looking for when you go back to edit your website’s styles later on down the road. This is where CSS comments can really come in handy. <a href="index.html?p=28" class="more-link" title="Permalink to: Use Comments to Organize Your CSS Design">Read more →</a></p>
              
              
              
              
              
